WEBVTT

00:03.069 --> 00:04.503
[ sighs ]

00:04.505 --> 00:08.741
It's about time.
I could eat a horse.
Okay.

00:08.743 --> 00:10.442
[ sighs ] anything?

00:10.444 --> 00:13.312
Just a beautiful morning
in texas.

00:16.349 --> 00:17.583
What is this?

00:17.585 --> 00:20.552
Those are
two chicken tacos.

00:20.554 --> 00:22.121
What?
That's what you ordered, right?

00:22.123 --> 00:23.322
No, I ordered chicken tinga.
[ chuckles ]

00:23.324 --> 00:24.757
This is chicken mole.

00:24.759 --> 00:27.493
Not to mention,
you put pico de gallo on them.

00:27.495 --> 00:30.062
You do realize that mole
is the sauce, right?

00:30.064 --> 00:32.431
You don't sauce the sauce,
seth,

00:32.433 --> 00:34.033
Unless you have
no taste buds

00:34.035 --> 00:35.501
Or you fail
to apply yourself.

00:35.503 --> 00:37.336
I'm just glad it's not
beef jerky and squeeze cheese.

00:37.338 --> 00:38.604
So...

00:38.606 --> 00:40.339
Five years
is a pretty long stretch.

00:40.341 --> 00:41.740
Mm-hmm.

00:41.742 --> 00:43.642
What did you do
with all that time, anyway?

00:43.644 --> 00:45.110
You know...

00:45.112 --> 00:47.246
You got to do the time
or the time does you.

00:47.248 --> 00:51.383
So...I told some stories,
heard some stories,

00:51.385 --> 00:52.618
Played dominos.

00:52.620 --> 00:54.319
You had five years
to improve yourself,

00:54.321 --> 00:55.454
And you played dominos.

00:55.456 --> 00:56.722
Is that why
I risked my ass

00:56.724 --> 00:58.257
To bust you
out of that prison transfer?

00:58.259 --> 01:00.259
This is what
I'm talking about, seth.

01:00.261 --> 01:02.094
You fail
to apply yourself.

01:02.096 --> 01:04.430
If it had been me in there,
I would have gotten a degree...

01:04.432 --> 01:05.798
Really?
...Maybe in engineering.

01:05.800 --> 01:07.332
If it had been you
in there,

01:07.334 --> 01:08.634
You would have got shivved
on your first day

01:08.636 --> 01:10.202
On account
of your piss-poor people skills.

01:10.204 --> 01:11.537
I don't need people skills.
I'm a prodigy.

01:11.539 --> 01:12.838
Oh, really? Really?

01:12.840 --> 01:14.807
Because you pissed off
everybody in the outfit.

01:14.809 --> 01:16.742
Nobody in k.C.
Will touch you.

01:16.744 --> 01:19.678
Last I heard, you're
living in some shack in
the woods near emporia.

01:19.680 --> 01:22.581
I guess that's how
a prodigy lives?
First of all,
who are you hearing that from?

01:22.583 --> 01:25.417
That courtney love
that you married for 10 seconds?
Hey!
Leave her out of this!

01:25.419 --> 01:27.119
And second of all,
do not dismiss the importance

01:27.121 --> 01:28.420
Of becoming self-sufficient.

01:28.422 --> 01:29.621
Look at the world around you,
brother.

01:29.623 --> 01:30.656
It's coming apart.

01:30.658 --> 01:32.391
Really?

01:33.726 --> 01:35.160
Oh, yeah.

01:35.162 --> 01:36.862
Yeah, doesn't look hunky-dory
at all.

01:36.864 --> 01:39.298
Okay, see? That's 'cause you've
been trapped in an 8x10 cell.

01:39.300 --> 01:41.166
You can't even
turn on the news these days

01:41.168 --> 01:42.668
Without seeing
some new catastrophe

01:42.670 --> 01:44.236
Of malthusian proportions.
Come on.

01:44.238 --> 01:46.772
And the man who cannot build
his own shelter

01:46.774 --> 01:49.708
Or gut his own food
is just courting disaster.

01:49.710 --> 01:50.843
What is that?

01:50.845 --> 01:52.544
Oh, this?

01:52.546 --> 01:53.812
This is my lucky blade.

01:53.814 --> 01:56.415
I won that
in a knife-throwing contest.

01:56.417 --> 01:59.184
This is a knife?

01:59.186 --> 02:00.219
Huh.

02:00.221 --> 02:02.721
Well,
how do you open it?

02:02.723 --> 02:03.856
Is there a button?

02:03.858 --> 02:05.724
I rest my case.

02:05.726 --> 02:08.327
So, they didn't have
any horchata?

02:08.329 --> 02:10.496
Hor-what?
Oh, come on, man.

02:10.498 --> 02:12.464
Delicious agua fresca,

02:12.466 --> 02:14.733
Made of rice, cinnamon,
and milk?
Oh, jesus christ.

02:14.735 --> 02:17.302
Okay, what the hell is it
with you and mexican
food all of a sudden?

02:17.304 --> 02:19.471
I mean, seriously, do you got
some new broad in your life

02:19.473 --> 02:20.539
You're not telling me about?

02:20.541 --> 02:21.807
Is her name carmen?

02:21.809 --> 02:23.542
Does she run
a burrito truck? What?

02:23.544 --> 02:25.477
Seth, all I'm saying is that
you need to apply yourself.

02:25.479 --> 02:27.212
Apply myself. Okay.

02:27.214 --> 02:30.282
Well, I'm about to apply my fist
to your goddamn face, okay?

02:30.284 --> 02:33.152
Eat your food.

02:33.154 --> 02:35.521
[ sniffles ]

02:35.523 --> 02:36.889
Just because
I live in the woods

02:36.891 --> 02:39.525
Doesn't mean that I can't
plan a job anymore.

02:39.527 --> 02:40.893
You should have let me
plan this one.

02:40.895 --> 02:43.195
Richard, listen to me.

02:43.197 --> 02:45.597
Now, it is a beautiful day
in the lone star state.

02:45.599 --> 02:48.467
So, why don't we just
celebrate my freedom

02:48.469 --> 02:50.369
And the undeniable fact

02:50.371 --> 02:53.839
That history is being made
right here, right now?

02:55.575 --> 02:59.211
The gecko brothers
ride again.

03:09.689 --> 03:12.257
You got your balls on?
Screwed on tight.

03:12.259 --> 03:13.492
Any son of a bitch
messes with you...

03:13.494 --> 03:15.394
You got my back.

03:15.396 --> 03:16.795
Here's to getting
rich and fat.

03:16.797 --> 03:19.298
And dying in the arms
of a beautiful woman.

03:21.935 --> 03:23.635
Good morning,
sweetheart.

03:59.439 --> 04:01.406
Woman on radio: <i>And now,</i>
<i>on a serious note, folks,</i>

04:01.408 --> 04:03.742
The department of public safety
<i>has just put out an advisory</i>

04:03.744 --> 04:06.445
<i>For two men reportedly behind</i>
<i>a violent bank robbery</i>

04:06.447 --> 04:07.946
<i>In abilene this morning.</i>

04:07.948 --> 04:09.448
<i>They're looking for two males,</i>

04:09.450 --> 04:10.983
<i>Late 20s,</i>
<i>wearing dark-blue suits,</i>

04:10.985 --> 04:12.784
<i>Believed to be armed</i>
<i>and dangerous.</i>

04:12.786 --> 04:14.987
[ radio tuning ]

04:14.989 --> 04:19.958
♪ oh, come, angel band

04:19.960 --> 04:24.663
♪ come
and around me stand ♪

04:24.665 --> 04:30.636
♪ oh, bear me away
on your snowy white wings ♪

04:30.638 --> 04:36.275
♪ to my immortal home

04:36.277 --> 04:37.943
Guess I should have used some
of that collection money

04:37.945 --> 04:40.312
For singing lessons.

04:40.314 --> 04:42.414
I don't think the congregation
could stand it, daddy.

04:43.549 --> 04:46.351
So, have you decided yet?
Are we going to the beach?

04:46.353 --> 04:47.919
Well, I don't likely know,
katie-kakes.

04:47.921 --> 04:49.588
Why, do you want to go
to a beach?

04:49.590 --> 04:51.723
What else is there to do
in mexico?

04:51.725 --> 04:53.592
Well, I'm sure
there's lots to do there.

04:53.594 --> 04:55.294
They do have beaches,

04:55.296 --> 04:57.829
But they also got mountains
and deserts and ruins.

04:57.831 --> 04:59.998
So, which one
are we going to?

05:00.000 --> 05:02.367
Wherever
the wind takes us.

05:02.369 --> 05:04.736
Come on.
Sing with me.

05:04.738 --> 05:07.639
♪ I am weak
but thou art strong ♪

05:07.641 --> 05:09.708
Yeah, right.
No, thanks.

05:09.710 --> 05:14.012
♪ jesus,
keep me from all wrong ♪

05:14.014 --> 05:15.580
[ cellphone chimes ]

05:18.384 --> 05:19.985
♪ I'll be --
who's that?

05:20.920 --> 05:22.354
Nobody.

05:22.356 --> 05:24.089
Is that that winthorp boy
from church?

05:24.091 --> 05:26.725
His name is kyle.

05:26.727 --> 05:29.494
And he just wants to know
when we're gonna be back.

05:29.496 --> 05:31.697
Kyle can wait.
As a matter of fact,

05:31.699 --> 05:35.467
Waiting is a fine skill
for him to acquire.

05:35.469 --> 05:38.070
Ha, ha. Very funny.

05:40.973 --> 05:44.543
Daddy...

05:44.545 --> 05:48.847
This whole thing, it's all
so sudden, don't you think?

05:48.849 --> 05:51.917
Well,
I prefer spontaneous.

05:51.919 --> 05:53.819
We're not gonna be gone
too long, right?

05:53.821 --> 05:55.687
I mean, we got school.

05:55.689 --> 05:58.657
Well, you and your brother
are both exceptional students.

05:58.659 --> 06:01.727
So you'll catch up, or
you'll go back to homeschooling.

06:01.729 --> 06:03.895
You're kidding me, right?

06:03.897 --> 06:05.831
It's my senior year, dad.

06:05.833 --> 06:09.468
I have homecoming
and -- and friends and...

06:09.470 --> 06:10.502
I have a life.

06:10.504 --> 06:11.937
You certainly do,

06:11.939 --> 06:15.040
With me and your brother,
right here on this r.V.

06:17.477 --> 06:18.577
[ sighs ]

06:24.150 --> 06:27.085
[ cellphone chimes ]

06:34.026 --> 06:35.861
[ toilet flushes ]

06:40.600 --> 06:43.468
[ sniffles ]

06:43.470 --> 06:45.470
Good lord.
Light a match!

06:45.472 --> 06:46.705
Only gonna get worse.

06:46.707 --> 06:48.039
And by the time we get
to mexico,

06:48.041 --> 06:49.608
This thing
is gonna be running

06:49.610 --> 06:50.942
On a whole different kind
of gas.

06:50.944 --> 06:51.977
You're disgusting.

06:51.979 --> 06:53.678
I'm awesome.

06:53.680 --> 06:56.948
Like these guys --
the sacred one, the hurricane.

06:56.950 --> 06:58.717
Can you even read that?

06:58.719 --> 07:00.652
I like the pictures.

07:00.654 --> 07:02.521
You know that stuff
is rigged, right?

07:02.523 --> 07:05.157
Yeah, but the rules are,
like, way looser down there.

07:05.159 --> 07:07.125
Also, the more
of a freak you are,

07:07.127 --> 07:09.027
The more popular
you become.

07:09.029 --> 07:10.862
[ cellphone chimes ]
hmm. Well, then you're gonna fit
right in.

07:12.498 --> 07:13.732
Give me that!
Give it back!

07:13.734 --> 07:16.668
"psalm 46:1."

07:16.670 --> 07:19.638
Ah, man.
Give it back to me,
please.

07:19.640 --> 07:22.507
You're like a classic freudian
test case, you know that?

07:22.509 --> 07:25.777
Preacher's daughter in love with
a boy who texts bible quotes.

07:25.779 --> 07:27.779
You write
stupid elvish poems.

07:27.781 --> 07:29.648
And you're basically
dating dad.

07:29.650 --> 07:31.450
Gross!

07:31.452 --> 07:33.518
Remind me again why mom and dad
walked halfway across china

07:33.520 --> 07:34.719
To adopt you.

07:34.721 --> 07:36.588
Hey, what's going on
back there?

07:36.590 --> 07:39.758
Uh, bible study, dad.

07:41.060 --> 07:43.628
So, has he told you
where we're going yet?

07:43.630 --> 07:44.663
Nope.

07:44.665 --> 07:46.498
Don't you want to know?

07:46.500 --> 07:47.899
Not really.

07:47.901 --> 07:50.802
But this whole trip
is totally schizo.

07:50.804 --> 07:52.170
Yeah.

07:52.172 --> 07:54.172
'cause you've been so normal
since mom died, right?

07:54.174 --> 07:55.974
It's been
just six months.

07:55.976 --> 07:58.009
People get weird
when someone dies.

07:58.011 --> 08:02.614
Weird like cutting your hair off
or getting drunk and stuff,

08:02.616 --> 08:05.050
Not buying a junky r.V.,
kidnapping your kids,

08:05.052 --> 08:07.519
And running to mexico.

08:07.521 --> 08:09.087
All right.
We're not running.

08:09.089 --> 08:11.990
And he didn't kidnap us.

08:11.992 --> 08:15.694
He just...Needs a break.

08:22.869 --> 08:25.070
So cool!
Scott.

08:25.072 --> 08:27.739
[ siren wailing in distance ]
uh, I think I hear
a fire truck coming.

08:27.741 --> 08:29.975
Well, we best
get out of their way.

08:37.083 --> 08:39.518
[ grunts ]

08:40.853 --> 08:41.987
[ sighs ]

08:45.591 --> 08:47.926
This is texas ranger
freddie gonzalez.

08:47.928 --> 08:49.261
I've got a ranger down,
a 10-70,

08:49.263 --> 08:51.630
At benny's world of liquor
on 83.

08:51.632 --> 08:52.731
[ sighs ]

08:52.733 --> 08:55.066
It's earl.

08:55.068 --> 08:56.902
Earl mcgraw.

08:56.904 --> 08:58.303
Requesting emergency backup

08:58.305 --> 09:00.739
And roadblocks
at all points due south.

09:00.741 --> 09:03.842
Suspects are abilene bank
robbers seth and richie gecko.

09:03.844 --> 09:07.145
They're driving a black 1960s
late-model mercury cougar.

09:07.147 --> 09:11.216
I'm 10-80 right now.

09:11.218 --> 09:13.084
[ tires screech ]

09:13.086 --> 09:14.252
Texas ranger!
Move over!

09:14.254 --> 09:15.887
Are you crazy?!
Move over!

09:23.262 --> 09:25.297
All right, let's move!
All right.

09:26.599 --> 09:27.699
Damn it.

09:27.701 --> 09:30.769
Get back in your cars.
They already passed you.

09:30.771 --> 09:33.038
How many cruisers you got?
Just the two right now.

09:33.040 --> 09:34.839
Block up
the 67 intersection.

09:34.841 --> 09:36.942
Radio ahead to get someone
at the 153 and 158 junctions.

09:36.944 --> 09:38.777
On it.
Let's get these moved.

09:38.779 --> 09:40.812
Get me my six
as soon as you can.

09:40.814 --> 09:44.616
Man: What happened back there?
Who we chasing?

09:44.618 --> 09:47.319
Monsters.

09:47.321 --> 09:51.156
Richie:
That liquor store had to be one
of our top-10 best exits ever.

09:51.158 --> 09:53.925
Maybe even top five.

09:53.927 --> 09:56.695
The way that booze
caught on fire,

09:56.697 --> 09:58.263
It was like bananas flambé.

09:58.265 --> 10:00.098
Even topped the bank.

10:00.100 --> 10:02.767
That liquor store was supposed
to be a quick piss stop,

10:02.769 --> 10:05.937
Not a goddamn
lee marvin moment.

10:05.939 --> 10:07.739
And we're heading
straight for the border.

10:07.741 --> 10:10.041
We got to get to el rey
before the cops get organized.

10:10.043 --> 10:12.210
You keep talking about
that place like it's the shit.

10:12.212 --> 10:13.945
Well,
that's 'cause it is.

10:13.947 --> 10:18.650
El rey means the king,
which is how we're gonna live.

10:18.652 --> 10:20.085
If we ever make it there.

10:20.087 --> 10:21.753
The border's still
an hour and a half away.

10:21.755 --> 10:23.788
By the time we get there,
it'll be swarming with badges.

10:23.790 --> 10:25.256
Well, then,
what do you suggest, einstein?

10:25.258 --> 10:28.793
Lay low, ditch the heat,
let the heat die down.

10:28.795 --> 10:30.895
There is no dying down.

10:30.897 --> 10:33.098
You just jacked it up
to high when you turned that
place into "the wild bunch."

10:33.100 --> 10:36.701
Lee marvin wasn't
in "the wild bunch."

10:36.703 --> 10:38.236
It was william holden.

10:38.238 --> 10:40.372
And every job
has its necessary casualties.

10:40.374 --> 10:42.173
No, richard.

10:42.175 --> 10:44.909
There was nothing necessary
about what happened back there.

10:44.911 --> 10:46.244
There was nothing necessary

10:46.246 --> 10:48.380
About what happened
in abilene, either.

10:48.382 --> 10:51.016
What happened to you
in that bank?

10:53.653 --> 10:56.021
You know, whenever I heard
stories in the clink

10:56.023 --> 10:57.722
About you losing your edge,

10:57.724 --> 10:59.858
Living out in the woods
like grizzly adams,

10:59.860 --> 11:01.092
I never really
believed them.

11:01.094 --> 11:02.727
Nah, no way. No.

11:02.729 --> 11:03.962
My brother's not really
a whack job.

11:03.964 --> 11:06.131
Don't call me that.
Are you on drugs?

11:07.400 --> 11:09.167
What?
You heard me.

11:09.169 --> 11:11.436
What, are you tweaking?
Pcp? Dope? What?
[ scoffs ]

11:11.438 --> 11:12.971
You know I don't go
for that shit.

11:12.973 --> 11:14.406
Then what the hell
is going on with you?

11:14.408 --> 11:16.274
You were supposed to
crack the vault,

11:16.276 --> 11:17.676
But you had to step away.

11:17.678 --> 11:19.144
Why?

11:19.146 --> 11:21.112
You used to be razor sharp.

11:21.114 --> 11:22.814
That's why you were so good
with the blade.
[ chuckles ]

11:22.816 --> 11:24.416
You know, it's funny
that you should mention that.

11:24.418 --> 11:26.017
Where the hell
is my knife?

11:26.019 --> 11:27.752
I got rid of it.
You did what?!

11:27.754 --> 11:29.287
I want it back.

11:29.289 --> 11:30.388
Well, it's gone.

11:40.299 --> 11:43.468
Santanico: <i>Richie.</i>

11:44.470 --> 11:46.204
I swear to god,

11:46.206 --> 11:47.906
I couldn't tell if you wanted
to rape those tellers

11:47.908 --> 11:49.407
Or cut them to pieces.

11:49.409 --> 11:51.076
<i>Come to me.</i>

11:51.078 --> 11:52.844
Something's coming.

11:52.846 --> 11:54.746
Something's coming? What?
What are you talking about?

11:54.748 --> 11:56.781
Something bad,
and you and the rest

11:56.783 --> 11:59.918
Are just a bunch of sheep
sleepwalking to the slaughter.

11:59.920 --> 12:01.152
Richie?

12:01.154 --> 12:02.187
<i>Richie.</i>

12:02.189 --> 12:03.488
[ banging ]

12:03.490 --> 12:05.156
Ah, shit.

12:05.158 --> 12:06.925
You hear it, too?

12:06.927 --> 12:10.028
It's the girl --
the bank teller.

12:10.030 --> 12:11.463
Remember?

12:21.841 --> 12:23.341
Where are you now?

12:23.343 --> 12:26.478
I don't know.
Somewhere on 83.

12:26.480 --> 12:29.481
He won't tell us
where we're going, kyle.

12:29.483 --> 12:31.182
He keeps acting
like we're on vacation,

12:31.184 --> 12:32.484
But he packed
all of our stuff.

12:32.486 --> 12:34.986
It doesn't matter.
I'm coming for you.

12:34.988 --> 12:37.155
Proverbs 3:15.

12:37.157 --> 12:39.891
"she is more precious
than jewels.

12:39.893 --> 12:43.228
And nothing you desire
can compare with her."

12:43.230 --> 12:45.330
You're crazy,
kyle winthorp.

12:45.332 --> 12:48.166
Crazy about you.

12:48.168 --> 12:50.301
I love you.

12:52.371 --> 12:54.472
I love you, too.

12:57.009 --> 13:00.111
I'll call you back,
all right?

13:00.113 --> 13:02.213
♪ home

13:04.984 --> 13:08.219
Dad, where's
your wedding ring?

13:08.221 --> 13:10.321
Oh, I, uh...

13:10.323 --> 13:13.158
I pawned it
to pay for the winnebago.

13:13.160 --> 13:15.160
You pawned
your wedding ring?!
Yep.

13:15.162 --> 13:17.362
And danny green gave me
top dollar for it, too.

13:17.364 --> 13:19.898
I thought about it long
and hard, believe you, me,

13:19.900 --> 13:22.100
But [sighs] I remember
what your mother said.

13:22.102 --> 13:24.135
"if I ever go before you do,

13:24.137 --> 13:26.137
Don't sit around
moping about me."

13:26.139 --> 13:28.306
So, you see, kate,

13:28.308 --> 13:31.276
She would have wanted us
to do this.

13:31.278 --> 13:35.146
In a way,
this is her gift to us.

13:35.148 --> 13:36.881
Gives us a chance
to explore

13:36.883 --> 13:38.950
And maybe find
our way home again.

13:41.821 --> 13:44.322
Daddy, I'm sorry.

13:44.324 --> 13:46.357
I guess
I'll never really know

13:46.359 --> 13:47.926
What it was like for you
that night,

13:47.928 --> 13:50.195
And I understand you
not wanting to talk about it.

13:50.197 --> 13:51.996
I already told you
what happened.

13:51.998 --> 13:54.265
My brakes needed replacing,

13:54.267 --> 13:56.434
And I was coming around
that bend off montgomery,

13:56.436 --> 13:58.903
And I saw a deer
and I swerved and --
no, that's --
that's not what I meant.

13:58.905 --> 14:01.306
I meant about your feelings,
about how you felt.

14:01.308 --> 14:03.875
About what you and mom
were talking about

14:03.877 --> 14:05.443
And why you were out
that night.

14:05.445 --> 14:08.112
Well, I don't see
why that matters.

14:08.114 --> 14:09.581
Well, it matters to <i>me.</i>

14:10.950 --> 14:12.317
Look,
I know you like to grieve

14:12.319 --> 14:14.886
Like you're alone
on an island sometimes,

14:14.888 --> 14:16.221
But you're not.

14:16.223 --> 14:20.258
We're here, too,
and we have a right to know.

14:20.260 --> 14:22.493
[ tires screech ]

14:24.597 --> 14:26.464
What the frack, dad?

14:26.466 --> 14:27.966
Okay.

14:27.968 --> 14:29.534
This is the last time
I'm gonna say this.

14:29.536 --> 14:33.605
I've told you both all I care
to say about that night.

14:33.607 --> 14:36.074
Now, the subject
is closed.

14:36.076 --> 14:38.443
Nothing good is gonna come out
of dwelling on it.

14:38.445 --> 14:40.645
Now, we're going
on this trip,

14:40.647 --> 14:43.381
And we're moving on
with our lives.

14:43.383 --> 14:45.049
Is that clear?

14:46.252 --> 14:48.519
You're right, dad.

14:48.521 --> 14:51.422
I won't ask
any more questions.

15:09.975 --> 15:11.109
[ sighs ]

15:11.111 --> 15:13.578
[ indistinct yelling ]

15:16.081 --> 15:18.016
Freddie:
I'll take it from here.

15:18.018 --> 15:19.350
Y'all okay?

15:19.352 --> 15:22.153
Look, I know
you must have been scared,

15:22.155 --> 15:23.621
But did you happen to hear
where they were headed?

15:23.623 --> 15:25.223
I didn't hear nothing.

15:25.225 --> 15:26.958
That's not totally true.

15:26.960 --> 15:28.393
You've got
to forgive my friend, sir.

15:28.395 --> 15:29.661
She's still
all weirded out

15:29.663 --> 15:31.496
From the way that freak
was messing with us.

15:31.498 --> 15:34.232
I just need to know if they said
anything before we got there,

15:34.234 --> 15:35.400
Anything about their plans.

15:35.402 --> 15:37.135
Seth, the normal one,

15:37.137 --> 15:40.271
He kept going into the back to
talk to some guy named carlos.

15:40.273 --> 15:42.540
Y'all happen to catch
a last name?
No, sir.

15:42.542 --> 15:45.443
But he seemed to be the one
planning it all.

15:45.445 --> 15:49.514
The other one, richie,
he was just psychotic.

15:49.516 --> 15:51.482
The freak drew on us
with a marker.

15:56.255 --> 15:57.355
Hold tight.

15:59.491 --> 16:01.259
[ siren wailing ]

16:22.047 --> 16:23.982
Under the circumstances,

16:23.984 --> 16:27.018
You did the best
you could, gonzalez.

16:27.020 --> 16:30.555
I have reason to believe that
the older of the two, richie,

16:30.557 --> 16:32.123
He's the cartel killer
we've been after.

16:32.125 --> 16:33.458
Now, hold on.

16:33.460 --> 16:35.393
A second ago,
they were just bank robbers.

16:35.395 --> 16:38.429
He drew the same symbol
we found at those crimes

16:38.431 --> 16:40.598
On those two witnesses here.

16:40.600 --> 16:42.333
That can't be
a coincidence.

16:42.335 --> 16:45.370
If I can just get a small detail
and some extra resources --

16:45.372 --> 16:48.106
There ain't gonna be no details,
no resources.
Sir! Sir!

16:48.108 --> 16:51.075
Come on, son. You know I have
to take you off of this.

16:51.077 --> 16:52.610
It's protocol.

16:52.612 --> 16:56.481
There's a reason
we got protocols, rules.

16:56.483 --> 16:58.216
Not just to protect us
from others,

16:58.218 --> 16:59.684
But to protect us
from ourselves.

16:59.686 --> 17:01.519
That's not
what earl taught me.

17:01.521 --> 17:03.755
Earl ain't here anymore.

17:05.224 --> 17:07.158
Now, I know it hurts.

17:07.160 --> 17:10.395
But trust me...

17:10.397 --> 17:13.364
We are gonna get
those sons of bitches.

17:13.366 --> 17:17.168
But right now,
you need to stand down.

17:17.170 --> 17:18.302
Go and be
with your family.

17:18.304 --> 17:20.171
Can you do that
for me?

17:22.508 --> 17:23.775
Yes, sir.

17:26.812 --> 17:29.514
Officers.

18:08.520 --> 18:09.854
Richie:
We're never gonna make it
across the border

18:09.856 --> 18:11.789
If she's back there
making all that racket.

18:11.791 --> 18:13.558
Yeah, this wouldn't
even be a problem if you
hadn't have brought her.

18:13.560 --> 18:15.560
If I hadn't have brought her,
we would both be pink mist

18:15.562 --> 18:17.128
On the side of that bank
in abilene.

18:17.130 --> 18:19.464
We do not take hostages
for a reason.

18:19.466 --> 18:21.232
It gets messy,
like tucson.

18:21.234 --> 18:22.733
That was tacoma.
Whatever!

18:22.735 --> 18:24.402
We should have just
left her at the door.

18:24.404 --> 18:26.671
But for some reason,
you had to bring her along.

18:26.673 --> 18:29.173
[ banging ]

18:29.175 --> 18:30.775
Nothing happened
at that bank.

18:30.777 --> 18:32.443
Then why did you bring her
to the bathroom?

18:32.445 --> 18:34.112
'cause I had to piss,
all right?

18:34.613 --> 18:35.646
You and your
goddamn rice milk.

18:35.648 --> 18:36.814
You came out of that john

18:36.816 --> 18:38.516
Looking like
jack fucking torrance.

18:39.184 --> 18:40.485
I want my knife back.

18:40.487 --> 18:41.853
Something happened
in that bank,

18:41.855 --> 18:43.354
Something
that got you killing,

18:43.356 --> 18:44.822
And you haven't stopped
since.

18:44.824 --> 18:47.892
<i>You can't trust him.</i>

18:47.894 --> 18:49.660
Now, you said
something's coming?

18:50.229 --> 18:51.863
What's coming, richard?

18:51.865 --> 18:53.564
What does that mean?
<i>Get rid of him.</i>

18:54.166 --> 18:55.666
You want me to kill him?

18:56.335 --> 18:59.604
Kill who? Jesus, richie,
who are you talking to?

18:59.606 --> 19:02.440
<i>Richie.</i>

19:02.442 --> 19:04.408
Stop the car.
What?

19:04.410 --> 19:05.710
No. I'm not --
do it now!

19:15.687 --> 19:18.689
[ suspenseful music plays ]

19:30.169 --> 19:31.602
[ sighs ]

19:31.604 --> 19:34.338
[ sighs ] oh, my god, monica.
You are a treasure.

19:34.340 --> 19:35.540
Yes, yes. Lindísima.

19:35.542 --> 19:38.242
Morning, violet.
Morning, irma.

19:45.817 --> 19:48.920
[ sighs ]

19:48.922 --> 19:50.922
All right.
[ sighs ]

19:50.924 --> 19:52.823
Happy payday, people.

19:52.825 --> 19:55.560
There you go.
For you.

19:56.528 --> 19:57.728
Always a happy day.

19:57.730 --> 19:59.497
Ibuenos días, abelardo!

19:59.499 --> 20:01.499
Buenos.
Aren't you on vacation?

20:01.501 --> 20:02.833
Yeah, tomorrow.

20:02.835 --> 20:06.537
Ah, you and leandro
must be, uh, really psyched.

20:06.539 --> 20:09.373
You know, a whole week alone
in hawaii?

20:09.375 --> 20:10.474
Huh?

20:11.476 --> 20:12.710
Except you're not.

20:12.712 --> 20:15.379
I am, it's just...
Things aren't great.

20:15.381 --> 20:16.747
Ain't that why
you go on vacation?

20:16.749 --> 20:18.282
[ chuckles ]

20:19.585 --> 20:20.618
Oh, my god.

20:20.620 --> 20:22.587
My daughter's phone.

20:22.589 --> 20:24.288
She must have left it
in here yesterday

20:24.290 --> 20:25.656
When she borrowed
my jacket.

20:25.658 --> 20:27.225
I'm telling you, abe.

20:27.227 --> 20:29.360
I may seem
like I have it together here,

20:29.362 --> 20:31.229
But the rest of my life's
<i>iválgame dios!</i>

20:31.231 --> 20:32.663
[ chuckles ]

20:32.665 --> 20:34.599
Between a daughter
who thinks she owns my wardrobe

20:34.601 --> 20:39.303
And a son [sighs]
who wants a rifle

20:39.305 --> 20:41.005
And a husband
who just got laid off,

20:41.007 --> 20:44.542
Work is vacation.

20:47.579 --> 20:48.713
Good morning,
sweetheart.

20:48.715 --> 20:50.848
[ gasps ]

20:50.850 --> 20:51.949
[ grunts ]

20:55.320 --> 20:56.954
Monica,
I didn't get my paycheck.

20:58.257 --> 20:59.490
You're gonna earn it
today.

20:59.492 --> 21:00.658
[ all gasping ]

21:10.469 --> 21:12.403
Surveillance drives.

21:18.310 --> 21:19.443
Clear.

21:23.315 --> 21:25.416
<i>Richie.</i>

21:25.418 --> 21:26.951
[ sniffles ]

21:29.621 --> 21:31.689
You got something
to say to me?

21:36.695 --> 21:38.396
Okay, listen up.

21:38.398 --> 21:41.299
Now, we are here to unburden
your vault of $30 million

21:41.301 --> 21:43.734
In bearer bonds that I have it
on very good authority

21:43.736 --> 21:45.002
You received last night

21:45.004 --> 21:47.405
Bound for oil companies
in the area.

21:47.407 --> 21:49.774
We're just gonna go ahead
and redistribute that wealth

21:49.776 --> 21:51.642
In our general direction.

21:51.644 --> 21:54.578
You people be nice about it,
nobody gets hurt.

21:56.982 --> 21:58.349
[ all gasp ]

21:59.985 --> 22:01.452
[ whimpers ]

22:01.454 --> 22:03.888
Nobody gets hurt?

22:03.890 --> 22:06.590
Lock the door.
Bring the guard.

22:08.994 --> 22:13.030
Okay. Cellphones. Come on.

22:13.032 --> 22:15.466
[ cellphones thud ]

22:15.468 --> 22:17.335
Very good.

22:17.337 --> 22:18.602
[ breathes shakily ]

22:18.604 --> 22:21.706
Where's your cellphone,
sister?

22:21.708 --> 22:23.374
In my purse over there.

22:34.419 --> 22:36.420
[ sighs ]

22:36.422 --> 22:37.955
Did you pat down
the women?
I did.

22:37.957 --> 22:39.657
I always pat down
the women.

22:39.659 --> 22:41.926
Relax.
I was a perfect gentleman.
Are you sure?

22:41.928 --> 22:43.694
'cause I've seen what time
in the slammer can do

22:43.696 --> 22:45.996
To a man's proclivities,
and we're not deviants, seth.

22:45.998 --> 22:47.932
Hmm.
We're bank robbers.

22:47.934 --> 22:49.433
Will you please go
bust the back door

22:49.435 --> 22:50.568
So we can have
an easy exit?

22:57.442 --> 22:58.776
Well, I'll be damned.

23:03.982 --> 23:06.050
[ sighs ]

23:08.854 --> 23:10.688
Seth:
Now, there's always a choice.

23:10.690 --> 23:14.425
You can choose right now to have
this be a quaint little story

23:14.427 --> 23:16.560
You tell your friends at parties
to help you get laid

23:16.562 --> 23:21.065
Or end up permanently disfigured
like your friend here.

23:21.067 --> 23:22.967
Now, lucky for you all,
I did my homework,

23:22.969 --> 23:25.403
And all I need right now
is the vault combo.

23:26.671 --> 23:28.639
I take it
you're mr. Milburn?

23:35.981 --> 23:38.149
You got to be shitting me.

23:40.752 --> 23:42.119
What the hell
are you doing?

23:42.121 --> 23:44.522
It's horchata, man.
I found it in the kitchen.

23:44.524 --> 23:45.856
Did you bust
the back door?

23:45.858 --> 23:47.892
Yeah,
let's hit the vault.

23:47.894 --> 23:49.160
We can't.

23:49.162 --> 23:51.028
You cold-cocked the guy
with the combo.

23:51.030 --> 23:52.663
All right, now plan "b."
check the usual...

23:52.665 --> 23:53.898
<i>Richie.</i>

23:57.436 --> 23:58.769
[ distantly ] hey.
[ snaps fingers ]

23:58.771 --> 23:59.870
Richie, pay attention.

24:01.039 --> 24:05.443
<i>She's the one. Take her.</i>

24:08.613 --> 24:10.915
Woman: No!
[ whimpers ]

24:10.917 --> 24:12.650
Please! Aah!

24:12.652 --> 24:14.084
Hey, hey!
Whoa! Whoa! Whoa! Whoa!

24:14.086 --> 24:15.619
Richie!
One of these ladies
knows it.

24:15.621 --> 24:17.154
[ whimpering ]

24:17.156 --> 24:18.622
Richie, listen to me.

24:21.893 --> 24:24.662
Stop!
I know the combo!

24:24.664 --> 24:26.564
I'll give it to you,
but you got to --

24:26.566 --> 24:28.732
You got to promise
not to hurt anybody!

24:33.638 --> 24:35.606
[ breathing heavily ]

24:45.083 --> 24:47.551
Hey, you stupid shit!

24:48.253 --> 24:49.620
You could've killed us!

24:52.724 --> 24:54.725
Hey, I'm talking to you.

24:54.727 --> 24:58.195
Don't you
walk away from me!

24:58.197 --> 25:00.164
Goddamn whack job.

25:03.268 --> 25:05.069
I'm not crazy.

25:07.639 --> 25:08.873
Oh, so that's
how it's gonna be, huh?

25:08.875 --> 25:11.609
You gonna kill me, richie?

25:11.611 --> 25:13.777
Like you were gonna kill
that teller?

25:22.187 --> 25:24.121
[ groans ]

25:24.856 --> 25:27.057
[ screams ]

25:27.059 --> 25:30.060
[ coughing ]

25:35.734 --> 25:37.801
[ strained ]
they were right.

25:37.803 --> 25:41.071
You really did go soft
while I was in --

25:45.844 --> 25:47.111
Oh! F--

25:57.188 --> 25:59.823
[ coughing ]

26:06.598 --> 26:09.767
Hey, I'm not done
with you yet!

26:18.777 --> 26:20.844
Jacob:
Okay, who's hungry?

26:23.214 --> 26:25.849
[ sighs ]

26:25.851 --> 26:28.085
Come on,
let's get something to eat.

26:28.087 --> 26:29.853
You want anything?

26:29.855 --> 26:31.822
I ain't hungry.

26:31.824 --> 26:34.291
Suit yourself.

26:42.167 --> 26:45.803
We're at some place
called bob's brisket off 83.

26:45.805 --> 26:48.339
You on your way?

26:48.341 --> 26:52.176
I'll take this seat.

26:56.815 --> 26:59.149
There's some woods
behind it.

26:59.151 --> 27:00.884
Looks like
there's a service road.

27:00.886 --> 27:03.787
I'll meet you back there.

27:09.027 --> 27:10.761
That's pretty good.
Hand me that sauce.

27:23.074 --> 27:24.708
[ cellphone ringing ]

27:24.710 --> 27:27.011
[ speaking spanish ]
seth:
Hey, it's me again.

27:27.013 --> 27:29.079
You call a lot, guero.

27:29.081 --> 27:31.649
Yeah, well, I still
got 10 million reasons
for you to answer.

27:31.651 --> 27:34.051
What happened now?
Richie happened.

27:34.053 --> 27:37.121
I probably shouldn't be
saying this, but...

27:37.123 --> 27:38.756
Something ain't right
with him.

27:38.758 --> 27:41.191
He is fine, seth.
Yeah,
you keep saying that.

27:41.193 --> 27:43.160
You keep telling me
that I'm supposed to trust him,

27:43.162 --> 27:45.195
But you're not here.
Listen to me, seth.

27:45.197 --> 27:47.297
I didn't front <i>you</i>
<i>for this job.</i>

27:47.299 --> 27:49.133
I fronted
los hermanos gecko.

27:49.135 --> 27:50.834
And it's a package deal.

27:50.836 --> 27:52.136
You got that?

27:52.138 --> 27:53.437
Well,
then help us get across.

27:53.439 --> 27:55.172
Or guess what.

27:55.174 --> 27:57.775
Neither you nor I nor him will
ever enjoy any of this money.

27:57.777 --> 28:00.010
Do you understand
what I'm saying?
<i>Chale.</i>

28:00.945 --> 28:02.312
I'm working on it.

28:02.314 --> 28:03.947
Now, wait a second,
d--

28:19.764 --> 28:21.999
[ chuckles ]
I ran out of gas.

28:22.001 --> 28:23.434
Hop in.

28:37.248 --> 28:38.415
So, uh...

28:38.417 --> 28:40.818
So how far
are you going?

28:40.820 --> 28:42.720
As far
as you'll take me.

28:42.722 --> 28:45.456
I can get you to bob's brisket,
about 10 miles down the road.

28:45.458 --> 28:48.425
Oh, for a midday repast?

28:48.427 --> 28:50.060
[ chuckling ] I don't know
what that is, sir,

28:50.062 --> 28:52.396
But I'm...
Fixing to get my girl back.

28:52.398 --> 28:54.498
Are you a religious man?

28:54.500 --> 28:56.233
Yes, sir, I am.

28:56.235 --> 28:58.402
Jesus christ is the one,
true god.

28:58.404 --> 29:00.237
Where I come from,
there's many.

29:00.239 --> 29:02.773
The soul chooses
its god.

29:02.775 --> 29:04.208
And it's what it does
in its service

29:04.210 --> 29:06.076
That gives that soul
its flavor.

29:06.078 --> 29:07.811
Flavor?
Oh, yes.

29:07.813 --> 29:09.947
You never heard of that?

29:09.949 --> 29:13.350
Souls are like...
Popsicles.

29:13.352 --> 29:15.319
Some are sweet,
some are bitter,

29:15.321 --> 29:18.088
Some are strong,
and some are weak.

29:18.090 --> 29:19.957
There's a whole rainbow
of kinds.

29:19.959 --> 29:22.459
Might as well come
in a variety pack.

29:22.461 --> 29:24.094
[ both chuckle ]

29:24.096 --> 29:29.800
Yeah, cherry-lime, peach-mango,
banana-strawberry.

29:29.802 --> 29:31.769
[ sighs ]

29:33.037 --> 29:34.838
What flavor are you,
kyle?

29:34.840 --> 29:36.807
Say what?

29:57.562 --> 29:59.163
[ bones creaking ]

30:04.035 --> 30:06.270
Cherry-lime.

30:11.009 --> 30:12.342
[ sighs ]

30:13.978 --> 30:15.312
[ sighs ]

30:17.148 --> 30:19.016
[ sighs ]

30:19.018 --> 30:20.984
You said you knew
the combo.
I-I swear that's right.

30:20.986 --> 30:22.953
At least I-it was last night.
What do you mean,
"last night"?

30:22.955 --> 30:25.522
There's a chance mr. Milburn may
have changed it this morning.

30:25.524 --> 30:27.090
What do you mean,
"changed it"?

30:31.095 --> 30:33.997
What is this,
a, uh, lando 190?

30:33.999 --> 30:38.368
Got 6 wheels, o-99 dial,
10 to 20 contact area --

30:38.370 --> 30:39.570
Nothing to sneer at.

30:41.973 --> 30:43.507
You're wasting your time.

30:43.509 --> 30:44.575
Ah, you don't know richie.

30:44.577 --> 30:46.376
This one time,

30:46.378 --> 30:48.245
We pulled a job on this
rock star in new york, right?

30:48.247 --> 30:50.914
He shall remain nameless for
statute-of-limitations reasons.

30:50.916 --> 30:53.450
Anyway, the safe
was in mick's studio, right?

30:53.452 --> 30:56.153
The guy has, like,
an entire floor on park avenue.

30:56.155 --> 30:57.855
Well, he's in there 24/7,

30:57.857 --> 30:59.189
Like, cutting tracks
or whatever the hell he does.

30:59.191 --> 31:00.891
And he basically
only ever leaves

31:00.893 --> 31:02.526
To go bang his girlfriend
in the next room, all right?

31:02.528 --> 31:05.229
So richie sneaks inside in
this giant-ass amp box, right?

31:05.231 --> 31:07.364
Shh!
Sorry, buddy.

31:07.366 --> 31:09.066
After, like, six hours,

31:09.068 --> 31:11.168
The dude finally leaves
to go bang his girlfriend.

31:11.170 --> 31:14.004
<i>Set me free.</i>

31:15.874 --> 31:18.342
<i>Set me free.</i>

31:22.447 --> 31:25.182
Turns out, the safe is on
the other side of the wall

31:25.184 --> 31:26.450
From mick's california king.

31:26.452 --> 31:28.051
This chick is loud.

31:28.053 --> 31:31.088
All right?
I'm talking rock-'n'-roll stuff.

31:31.090 --> 31:33.190
It's nuts.

31:33.192 --> 31:34.391
And obviously,
richie here...

31:34.393 --> 31:36.093
I mean,
he needs quiet, right?

31:36.095 --> 31:38.629
He starts timing his work
to their rhythm.

31:38.631 --> 31:41.398
<i>Set me free.</i>

31:43.968 --> 31:46.103
We make off with a deuce
and a half in watches.

31:46.105 --> 31:47.971
So, don't judge
before you know.

31:50.508 --> 31:52.442
<i>Set me free.</i>

31:52.444 --> 31:54.344
<i>Set me free.</i>

31:56.247 --> 31:58.482
Richie, are you okay?

31:58.484 --> 31:59.583
I can't work like this.

31:59.585 --> 32:01.251
Okay, okay. I'm sorry.
It's my bad.

32:01.253 --> 32:02.586
Just -- just relax.

32:02.588 --> 32:04.421
Don't talk to me
like I'm a child.

32:04.423 --> 32:05.956
Okay, we're cool.

32:05.958 --> 32:07.457
I brought the drill
just in case, all right?

32:07.459 --> 32:09.359
Now, go find
some of that rice milk,

32:09.361 --> 32:12.629
Take her back to the hostages,
and just...Chill out.

32:15.600 --> 32:17.334
[ sighs ]

32:18.569 --> 32:19.703
[ drill whirs ]

32:27.278 --> 32:29.146
[ sighs ]

32:29.148 --> 32:31.248
I can crack a safe.

32:31.250 --> 32:33.450
I can plan a job.

32:35.386 --> 32:37.354
Please...Don't hurt me.

32:37.356 --> 32:42.025
<i>Richie.</i>

32:42.027 --> 32:43.994
You're right, you know.
Shut up.

32:43.996 --> 32:46.430
<i>Cut her.</i>

32:47.999 --> 32:49.433
[ sighs ]

32:49.435 --> 32:50.634
It's like
he doesn't trust you.

32:50.636 --> 32:52.436
If you know
what's good for you,

32:52.438 --> 32:54.471
You'll shut your mouth
right now.

32:56.507 --> 32:58.108
Are you sure
you can trust him?

33:01.179 --> 33:02.346
Cut her.

33:03.548 --> 33:05.349
Cut her.

33:08.720 --> 33:10.988
[ whimpers ]

33:10.990 --> 33:15.058
[ voice breaking ]
please, no. No.

33:15.060 --> 33:16.460
I have a family.

33:16.462 --> 33:19.096
Set me free.

33:22.066 --> 33:23.266
You want me
to set you free?

33:26.004 --> 33:30.040
Please, I have a son
and a daughter.

33:31.609 --> 33:33.110
It's all right.

33:35.613 --> 33:37.147
Do it.

33:37.149 --> 33:39.583
[ alarm blaring ]

33:39.585 --> 33:41.651
[ panting ]

33:46.224 --> 33:48.625
What did you do?
Me?!

33:52.096 --> 33:55.632
Give me that.
[ siren wailing ]

33:55.634 --> 33:56.733
Shit!

33:58.236 --> 34:01.471
Well, lucky for us
you busted the back door.

34:03.341 --> 34:04.674
You didn't bust
the back door.

34:10.481 --> 34:13.750
Officer:
Come out with your hands up!

34:15.520 --> 34:17.654
<i>She knows.</i>

34:17.656 --> 34:19.189
Open it.

34:19.191 --> 34:20.724
I know you can.

34:22.560 --> 34:24.795
I'd rather watch you burn.

34:31.803 --> 34:33.770
[ buzzer, door unlocks ]

34:33.772 --> 34:34.805
How the hell
did you do that?

34:34.807 --> 34:37.207
Got your balls on?

34:37.209 --> 34:38.675
Screwed on tight.

34:38.677 --> 34:41.078
[ whimpering ]

34:47.251 --> 34:48.852
[ sighs ]

35:26.524 --> 35:27.791
Richie!

35:30.728 --> 35:32.295
Put that thing down!

35:32.864 --> 35:36.566
Why the hell
would you pick that up?

35:36.568 --> 35:38.335
I thought
she wanted me to.

35:38.337 --> 35:41.271
She?

35:43.608 --> 35:45.575
What's happening to me?

35:45.577 --> 35:48.678
We'll stop.
All right?

35:48.680 --> 35:51.581
We'll stop, we'll, uh,
we'll ditch the car,

35:51.583 --> 35:52.782
We'll get rid
of the teller.

35:52.784 --> 35:55.752
And whatever's going on
with you...

35:55.754 --> 35:57.454
We'll fix it.

35:57.456 --> 35:59.723
Okay?

35:59.725 --> 36:01.358
Now, put down
the goddamn dog,

36:01.360 --> 36:02.626
And I'll get you one of those
kahuna burgers you like.

36:03.628 --> 36:05.829
Okay.

36:05.831 --> 36:09.533
Hey, you all right?

36:21.479 --> 36:24.581
What's all this?

36:24.583 --> 36:25.949
That's the last bank footage
they got uploaded

36:25.951 --> 36:27.450
Before they shot the drive.

36:27.452 --> 36:28.652
I think one of these guys

36:28.654 --> 36:30.387
Is the cartel killer
I've been after.

36:30.389 --> 36:32.522
<i>You've</i> been after?

36:32.524 --> 36:34.224
Baby, I'm trying
to get a lead here

36:34.226 --> 36:35.859
Before these guys disappear
into mexico.

36:35.861 --> 36:38.695
Half the state of texas
is sniffing them out.

36:38.697 --> 36:40.664
What are you gonna do
sticking your nose in?

36:40.666 --> 36:42.899
I'll do plenty.
That's what I'm trained to do.

36:43.935 --> 36:45.902
Trained by the best.

36:45.904 --> 36:49.806
Baby, I know you're all torn up
about this.

36:49.808 --> 36:52.742
But I worry about you
going out there seeing red.

36:52.744 --> 36:54.811
You're gonna
get yourself hurt.

36:54.813 --> 36:56.546
512.

36:56.548 --> 36:57.948
What?

36:57.950 --> 36:59.916
512 days.

36:59.918 --> 37:02.519
That's how long
I spent with earl.

37:02.521 --> 37:04.421
And that's just
since we've been partners.

37:04.423 --> 37:06.556
Hell, I've known that man
since little league.

37:06.558 --> 37:08.692
He got me
my first pair of cleats.

37:08.694 --> 37:11.294
I spent more time with that man
than anyone.

37:11.296 --> 37:12.762
Including his family.

37:12.764 --> 37:14.397
[ baby cries ]

37:15.833 --> 37:17.234
What about <i>your</i> family?

37:25.610 --> 37:26.977
Okay.

37:26.979 --> 37:29.779
Oh, I know. Come here.

37:32.316 --> 37:33.650
Yeah.

37:33.652 --> 37:37.254
You know, your daddy
can be a little thickheaded.

37:37.256 --> 37:40.423
I love you and your mama more
than anything in this world,

37:40.425 --> 37:41.691
But I made a promise
to earl.

37:43.928 --> 37:46.663
Now, that don't look right,
does it, sweetie?

37:48.566 --> 37:51.601
Says here abilene pd found
all the employee cellphones.

37:51.603 --> 37:54.604
So whose phone is that
she's holding?

37:54.606 --> 37:57.841
With a cute, little, pink,
bunny case.

38:04.949 --> 38:09.653
[ cellphone ringing ]

38:09.655 --> 38:12.789
I thought you grabbed
all the phones.
I did.

38:17.461 --> 38:19.362
[ whimpering ]

38:23.901 --> 38:25.869
Freddie:
Mrs. Garza?

38:25.871 --> 38:27.671
Well, if it ain't tonto.

38:27.673 --> 38:28.905
Where is she,
you son of a bitch?

38:28.907 --> 38:30.307
[ screams ]

38:30.309 --> 38:31.474
She's a little tied up
at the moment.

38:31.476 --> 38:32.842
Let me make this
real simple --

38:32.844 --> 38:34.577
You touch her,
I will personally make sure

38:34.579 --> 38:36.346
You spend so much time
in the hole,

38:36.348 --> 38:37.981
Your own brother won't
recognize you when you get out.

38:37.983 --> 38:40.517
Well, you got
to catch me first.

38:40.519 --> 38:41.885
What are you thinking?

38:46.090 --> 38:47.324
Did you get that, tony?

38:47.326 --> 38:48.992
Tony: Got it.
Yes!

38:59.637 --> 39:00.837
[ shotgun chambers ]

39:04.475 --> 39:07.510
Ferdinand?

39:07.512 --> 39:09.913
I'm making pot roast.

39:14.819 --> 39:16.553
I'll be home
for dinner.

39:16.555 --> 39:19.556
Careful.

39:20.725 --> 39:23.927
[ door opens, closes ]

39:27.998 --> 39:29.833
Scott:
Kate, come back!

39:29.835 --> 39:31.568
Where are you,
katie-kates?

39:41.579 --> 39:43.079
Kate,
w-what are you doing?

39:44.081 --> 39:45.682
Kate,
what the hell?

39:46.684 --> 39:48.685
You were gonna leave <i>me,</i>
<i>too?</i>

39:50.421 --> 39:51.821
What's going on here?

39:51.823 --> 39:55.458
She texted him.
I saw her.

39:55.460 --> 39:56.926
Tattletale.

39:56.928 --> 39:59.963
Sorry you had to drive
all the way out here, son.

39:59.965 --> 40:02.098
I do appreciate your concern
for my daughter.

40:02.100 --> 40:04.100
This is a family matter.

40:04.102 --> 40:05.769
It's none of your business.

40:05.771 --> 40:09.739
With all due respect,
kate made it my business.

40:09.741 --> 40:11.875
She's downright scared
the way you just packed her up

40:11.877 --> 40:13.543
And took her out of her life
like that.

40:13.545 --> 40:15.445
Now, listen,
I know your family

40:15.447 --> 40:17.147
For a long time now
from church,

40:17.149 --> 40:18.848
And I don't want
to have to call them up

40:18.850 --> 40:20.583
On account of you giving me
any kind of trouble out here.

40:20.585 --> 40:22.485
Go ahead.
Daddy,
don't you dare.

40:22.487 --> 40:23.753
Call them.

40:23.755 --> 40:26.756
Now, kyle,
you're a good boy.

40:26.758 --> 40:28.091
Don't do anything
to betray that.

40:28.093 --> 40:30.827
You're the traitor,
reverend.

40:30.829 --> 40:34.731
What kind of man up and abandons
his congregation?

40:36.133 --> 40:37.434
Abandons it?

40:37.436 --> 40:39.436
What's he talking about,
dad?

40:39.438 --> 40:42.005
He didn't tell you?
I talked to my mom.

40:42.007 --> 40:43.973
He quit the parish
for good.

40:43.975 --> 40:46.509
You said
it was just a break.

40:46.511 --> 40:49.579
When were you
gonna tell us?

40:50.915 --> 40:53.049
Soon as the time
was right.

40:53.051 --> 40:55.618
But why, dad?

40:55.620 --> 40:56.953
Why would you quit?

40:58.989 --> 41:00.190
Answer him.

41:01.859 --> 41:04.794
Answer him,
or I swear to god,

41:04.796 --> 41:08.965
I will get in kyle's truck,
and I will never look back.

41:08.967 --> 41:12.669
If you're a man of the cloth,
be it any cloth,

41:12.671 --> 41:15.238
Not a day goes by that
you don't look in the mirror

41:15.240 --> 41:16.773
And wonder,
"am I a fraud?"

41:16.775 --> 41:19.676
What are you
talking about, dad?

41:19.678 --> 41:22.545
A shepherd
can't lead his flock

41:22.547 --> 41:25.014
If he's lost the path
himself.

41:25.016 --> 41:27.484
Are you saying
that you don't believe anymore?

41:30.955 --> 41:32.622
I told you, come on.
Let's go now!

41:32.624 --> 41:33.690
Let go of her.

41:33.692 --> 41:35.058
Young man, let go of her.

41:35.060 --> 41:36.593
Let go of her,
young man!

41:37.695 --> 41:39.963
Kyle! Kyle, stop it!
Stop it!

41:39.965 --> 41:42.065
What are you doing?!

41:44.568 --> 41:46.169
What has gotten into you?!

41:46.171 --> 41:47.570
Don't let him
fool you!

41:47.572 --> 41:49.005
He's my dad!

41:53.577 --> 41:56.246
I want you to leave.
Now!

41:56.248 --> 41:58.815
Fine. So long.

41:58.817 --> 42:01.184
You and your
rice-monkey brother.

42:01.186 --> 42:02.552
No! No!

42:03.921 --> 42:05.655
Bunch of freaks.

42:05.657 --> 42:07.857
You deserve each other.

42:07.859 --> 42:11.060
Let's go, kids.
Come on, let's go.

42:28.546 --> 42:31.080
You've done good,
cherry-lime.

42:34.118 --> 42:36.319
[ engine turns over ]

43:53.831 --> 43:56.199
Richie:
Got your balls on?
Seth:
Screwed on tight.

43:58.102 --> 44:01.638
Don't shoot
or I'll kill her!

44:01.640 --> 44:02.972
[ whimpering ]

44:10.714 --> 44:13.316
[ tires screech,
siren wailing ]

44:43.080 --> 44:45.848
[ tires squeal ]

44:54.324 --> 44:56.359
Hey.

44:56.361 --> 44:58.394
Richie.

45:01.031 --> 45:02.832
Here's to getting
rich and fat.

45:02.834 --> 45:05.168
[ chuckles ]

45:05.170 --> 45:08.204
And dying in the arms
of a beautiful woman.

45:14.912 --> 45:17.013
That's right.
